{
  "name": "visualize-audio-waveforms-on-20260406-0611",
  "idea": "Visualize audio waveforms on the video editor timeline. When a track contains audio (either an audio track or a video track with audio), render a waveform visualization on top of the clip in the timeline UI. This should show the audio amplitude over time so users can see where audio peaks/silences are when editing. Should work for both dedicated audio tracks and video clips that have embedded audio. The waveform data infrastructure already exists via AudioDataProvider and @remotion/media-utils (getAudioData) in the art-agents audio-reactive plan \u2014 but the reigh-app video editor is the current active codebase. Key files: reigh-app/src/tools/video-editor/components/TimelineEditor/ (timeline UI), reigh-app/src/tools/video-editor/compositions/AudioTrack.tsx, reigh-app/src/tools/video-editor/types/, reigh-app/src/tools/video-editor/hooks/. The timeline uses a canvas-based renderer (TimelineCanvas.tsx) for clip rendering.",
